and I was thinking if
they try anything else,

47:16.275 --> 47:17.908
I can just escape out
through the window

47:17.910 --> 47:19.209
'cause it wasn't even locked.

47:19.211 --> 47:20.711
And you think it
still might be open?

47:20.713 --> 47:22.713
Yeah, I mean lots of people
leave their bathroom window

47:22.715 --> 47:24.180
open all the time.

47:24.182 --> 47:25.615
Sneaking in there like that,
isn't that kind of risky?

47:25.617 --> 47:27.117
Of course it's risky.

47:27.119 --> 47:29.153
But what do I care about
a little thing like risk?

47:29.155 --> 47:31.055
I mean I'm not gonna let
something like that stop us

47:31.057 --> 47:32.957
from getting where
we need to be.

47:32.959 --> 47:34.591
I mean I'm just not
that kind of a person.

47:34.593 --> 47:36.292
We should go now?

47:36.294 --> 47:37.528
Now?

47:37.530 --> 47:38.461
I mean the guards
are probably sleeping,

47:38.463 --> 47:39.729
and at this time of night,

47:39.731 --> 47:41.599
we could be there and
back with the uniforms

47:41.601 --> 47:42.832
in less than an hour.

47:42.834 --> 47:45.135
Yeah, yeah, I mean
we probably could,

47:45.137 --> 47:47.671
but I mean the other
thing we could do is

47:47.673 --> 47:50.307
we could just stay here and,
you know, take advantage

47:50.309 --> 47:53.077
of these really exciting
feelings that we're having.

47:53.079 --> 47:55.613
No, no, no, this
is too exciting.

47:55.615 --> 47:56.680
Come on, get up.

47:56.682 --> 47:58.651
We are stealing garda uniforms.

48:00.952 --> 48:02.218
Yeah.

48:12.631 --> 48:14.298
Well even
if it's not open,

48:14.300 --> 48:15.499
we'll have to find
another way in.

48:15.501 --> 48:16.334
Yeah.

48:17.736 --> 48:19.269
And you're
sure they don't have guns?

48:19.271 --> 48:21.338
No, guards in
Ireland never carry guns.

48:21.340 --> 48:22.573
Well how
do they shoot people?

48:22.575 --> 48:25.341
- They don't.
- Well what do they do?

48:25.343 --> 48:27.244
I don't know,
they have truncheons.

48:27.246 --> 48:28.879
Oh, and
those have bullets?

48:28.881 --> 48:30.513
- No, of course not.
- Oh.

48:30.515 --> 48:31.649
But if
you got over the head

48:31.651 --> 48:32.816
with one of those things,

48:32.818 --> 48:33.883
it could really crack
open your skull.

48:33.885 --> 48:34.887
Oh, okay.

48:37.456 --> 48:39.756
Okay, so what I'm gonna do
is I'm just gonna go in there,

48:39.758 --> 48:41.358
I'm gonna grab the
uniforms and be back...

48:41.360 --> 48:42.792
No, no, no, no, I
should go in there.

48:42.794 --> 48:43.593
I'm gonna fit more easily
through the window.

48:43.595 --> 48:44.394
No, you're not.

48:44.396 --> 48:45.928
And anyway it's my idea,

48:45.930 --> 48:47.463
so I should be the
one who goes in there.

48:47.465 --> 48:48.999
Why wouldn't I fit more
easily through the window?

48:49.001 --> 48:50.834
Well because even though
I have broader shoulders,

48:50.836 --> 48:53.037
I can just pull them in, and
once I get past my chest,

48:53.039 --> 48:54.805
I don't have any hips
to worry about, so...

48:54.807 --> 48:55.707
And I do?

48:57.142 --> 49:00.244
No, no, no you don't,
I didn't mean that, I...

49:00.246 --> 49:03.546
Okay, fine, so the
uniforms are at the end

49:03.548 --> 49:04.881
of the kitchen table?

49:04.883 --> 49:06.350
Yeah, yeah,
yeah, well at least

49:06.352 --> 49:07.850
that's where they hung
them the day I was there,

49:07.852 --> 49:09.952
and I assume
they're still there.

49:09.954 --> 49:12.523
Actually I can just
make them out from here.

49:12.525 --> 49:13.957
They hung their hats
and their jackets.

49:13.959 --> 49:16.126
I think actually their
shirts are in there as well.

49:16.128 --> 49:18.662
I could grab them, and I
could be out in five seconds,

49:18.664 --> 49:20.698
I mean, and actually I
could even open that door

49:20.700 --> 49:22.765
from the inside and come
straight out this way.

49:22.767 --> 49:24.600
I...

49:24.602 --> 49:26.903
What, what are you doing?

49:26.905 --> 49:30.341
What, Nicole, come
back, come back.

49:30.343 --> 49:31.610
You locked the window?

49:34.347 --> 49:35.448
Kieran, is that you?

49:36.715 --> 49:37.549
What?

49:38.651 --> 49:40.953
- I said is that you?
- Course it is.

49:41.820 --> 49:42.854
Who else would it be.

49:45.057 --> 49:47.791
Okay, God, I know we
haven't communicated

49:47.793 --> 49:51.729
in a really long time, and
well it's mostly your fault.

49:51.731 --> 49:54.365
I mean in fairness,
you're very aloof.

49:54.367 --> 49:58.434
But if you do happen to exist,

49:58.436 --> 50:01.004
maybe you could
just first of all

50:01.006 --> 50:02.441
just get Nicole out of this

50:09.648 --> 50:12.883
and then maybe make
it so that she,

50:12.885 --> 50:15.354
she, you understand what I mean.

50:26.398 --> 50:27.898
I know you're single
and everything,

50:27.900 --> 50:29.966
and maybe it works for you,

50:29.968 --> 50:33.539
but I don't think it'd
be very good for me.

50:51.523 --> 50:52.756
No, no, no, no, go, go back.

51:15.247 --> 51:16.148
Sh, sh, sh.

51:46.611 --> 51:49.012
Have you got
butterflies in your belly?

51:49.014 --> 51:51.717
No, but your coat
is really smelly.

51:52.651 --> 51:54.119
You don't look very steady.

51:56.222 --> 51:59.555
Well I don't think
you're really ready.

51:59.557 --> 52:00.657
What do you want?

52:00.659 --> 52:02.792
- A mani/pedi?
- What's a mani/pedi?

52:02.794 --> 52:04.428
It's a manicure pedicure.

52:04.430 --> 52:06.296
Abbreviations don't count.

52:06.298 --> 52:07.497
Oh really?

52:07.499 --> 52:09.166
Yeah, sorry.

52:09.168 --> 52:11.135
- Oh, why not?
- They just don't.

52:12.438 --> 52:14.937
Right, should we do this?

52:14.939 --> 52:16.342
Yeah, let's do it.

52:17.910 --> 52:21.512
All right, good
luck Officer McCarthy.

52:21.514 --> 52:22.945
Thank you, Ma'am.

52:22.947 --> 52:24.247
Although I probably
shouldn't use my real name.

52:24.249 --> 52:25.416
Yeah, probably not.

52:26.885 --> 52:28.151
You're gonna do
most of the talking, right?

52:28.153 --> 52:29.852
Don't worry,
we'll be grand.

52:29.854 --> 52:31.287
Are you sure?

52:31.289 --> 52:34.423
Of course, sure
those nuns are easily fooled.

52:39.197 --> 52:40.229
Thank you
very much, sister.

52:40.231 --> 52:41.599
You're very welcome.

52:42.901 --> 52:45.604
So how can I be of assistance?

52:46.771 --> 52:49.305
Well Sister, we're
gathering information

52:49.307 --> 52:52.108
with regards to monies
that went missing

52:52.110 --> 52:53.545
over this past weekend.

52:54.579 --> 52:55.945
Monies?

52:55.947 --> 52:58.582
Well, yes monies.

52:58.584 --> 53:01.017
I mean it is money,

53:01.019 --> 53:04.687
but there happens to be two
different currencies involved,

53:04.689 --> 53:09.258
so it may be more
appropriate to say monies.

53:09.260 --> 53:11.562
The majority of it is in euro,

53:11.564 --> 53:15.666
but there happens to be some
Irish pounds in there as well.

53:15.668 --> 53:17.533
Irish pounds you say?

53:17.535 --> 53:18.801
I do, Sister, yes.

53:18.803 --> 53:21.704
And so we were wondering
if you might have come

53:21.706 --> 53:25.242
into contact with said
monies at any stage

53:25.244 --> 53:27.079
during the last weekend?

53:28.479 --> 53:29.713
Do you know something?

53:29.715 --> 53:32.448
You look very familiar to me.

53:32.450 --> 53:33.283
I do?

53:33.285 --> 53:34.486
Yes, you do.

53:35.720 --> 53:37.620
Well you've
probably seen me out

53:37.622 --> 53:41.191
and about you know,
on my, my beat.

53:41.193 --> 53:44.162
Hm, that's probably
it all right.

53:45.363 --> 53:47.698
As I was saying, Sister,

53:47.700 --> 53:49.633
we were wondering
if you may have come

53:49.635 --> 53:54.640
into contact with the
aforementioned monies in question?

53:56.008 --> 53:58.207
You'd wonder why would anyone
have Irish pounds on them

53:58.209 --> 53:59.675
in this day and age.

53:59.677 --> 54:03.113
I mean they'd be of hardly
any value at all, would they?

54:03.115 --> 54:07.651
No, they probably wouldn't,
but as for the 20,000 euro,

54:07.653 --> 54:09.988
now that would definitely
have a value of,

54:10.889 --> 54:14.793
well of 20,000 euro.

54:16.028 --> 54:18.263
You're probably right there.

54:20.064 --> 54:21.597
Are you absolutely sure

54:21.599 --> 54:24.901
that yourself and myself
haven't met somewhere before?

54:24.903 --> 54:26.836
Yes, Sister, I am.

54:26.838 --> 54:27.838
And where would you be from?

54:27.840 --> 54:29.972
I'm from here,
from, from Cork.

54:29.974 --> 54:33.443
You don't seem to have
a very strong Cork accent.

54:33.445 --> 54:34.977
Well, I used to live abroad,

54:34.979 --> 54:37.079
and you see my wife
is a foreigner.

54:37.081 --> 54:41.417
You know sometimes I tend
to pick up things, you know.

54:41.419 --> 54:42.919
Is that right?

54:42.921 --> 54:46.756
So, Sister, if
you have information

54:46.758 --> 54:49.760
that might help us
with our investigation,

54:49.762 --> 54:51.830
we would really
like you to tell us.

54:53.231 --> 54:56.101
You wouldn't be Mary
McCarthy's son, would you?

54:57.369 --> 55:00.104
No, Sister, no, no I wouldn't.

55:01.305 --> 55:02.506
Well then whose
son would you be?

55:02.508 --> 55:05.908
I'd be Mary,
Mary Murphy's son.

55:05.910 --> 55:08.544
See, she'd be my
mother, you see,

55:08.546 --> 55:12.015
and so then I'd be her son.

55:12.017 --> 55:14.483
Now it is believed to
have been dropped off

55:14.485 --> 55:16.919
on the steps of
this very convent

55:16.921 --> 55:19.655
by a five-foot brown-haired
man who happened

55:19.657 --> 55:22.459
to be driving a bicycle.

55:22.461 --> 55:24.894
You know Mary
McCarthy's son was married

55:24.896 --> 55:27.363
to a foreigner as well.

55:27.365 --> 55:28.298
Really?

55:28.300 --> 55:30.267
I think she was an American.

55:30.269 --> 55:31.734
I remember it clearly now.

55:31.736 --> 55:35.405
A few months before
Mary McCarthy died,

55:35.407 --> 55:37.506
I heard her son was
getting married,

55:37.508 --> 55:40.242
and I said I'll pop my
head into the church

55:40.244 --> 55:42.379
just for the ceremony.

55:42.381 --> 55:45.515
And it was only when the
bride was saying her vows

55:45.517 --> 55:48.617
that I realized
where she was from.

55:48.619 --> 55:51.954
My wife is definitely
not an American, so...

55:51.956 --> 55:53.557
- No.
- No, she...

55:53.559 --> 55:55.194
Do you know
something about me?

55:56.394 --> 55:59.361
I've been teaching in
the primary school here

55:59.363 --> 56:02.233
for the last 42 years.

56:03.367 --> 56:05.167
And when you've been
teaching young children

56:05.169 --> 56:08.104
of that age for
as long as I have,

56:08.106 --> 56:10.640
you develop an impeccable sense

56:10.642 --> 56:15.647
of when someone is being
genuine and when they're not.

56:19.918 --> 56:23.919
Now I mustn't be late
for mass, gentlemen.

56:23.921 --> 56:25.421
It's very important
for someone like me

56:25.423 --> 56:28.057
to set a good example to the
rest of the congregation.

56:28.059 --> 56:33.064
Just like your mother,
God rest her soul,

56:34.265 --> 56:36.235
believed she was setting
a good example for you.

56:39.070 --> 56:42.206
And you can rest
assured, gentlemen,

56:43.608 --> 56:48.246
that any and all information
I possess on the matter,

56:49.680 --> 56:54.218
I will divulge to Sergeant
O'Connell himself directly.

57:07.698 --> 57:10.166
The other Irish
pounds, we should,

57:10.168 --> 57:12.434
we should probably burn them.

57:12.436 --> 57:14.504
Brendan, if she's
called the police,

57:14.506 --> 57:16.539
they can be here in
like 10 seconds flat.

57:16.541 --> 57:18.207
Yeah, yeah, I know that,

57:18.209 --> 57:20.943
but Nicole you're not gonna
have to worry about that

57:20.945 --> 57:22.345
'cause I just
booked you a ticket.

57:22.347 --> 57:23.280
What?

57:23.282 --> 57:24.213
Yeah, and I used everything

57:24.215 --> 57:25.715
that was in our savings account,

57:25.717 --> 57:27.416
and it's a nonrefundable
ticket, so you have to go.

57:27.418 --> 57:30.452
Huh, no, I'm not
going anywhere.

57:30.454 --> 57:33.256
God, I can't believe we
didn't get rid of these.

57:33.258 --> 57:34.658
Look I tried to get
you on an earlier one,

57:34.660 --> 57:35.725
but the earliest
one I could get is

57:35.727 --> 57:37.227
at seven o'clock tomorrow night,

57:37.229 --> 57:39.528
so all you have to do is
just lay low for 24 hours,

57:39.530 --> 57:41.430
and then you'll be safely
on your way back to America.

57:41.432 --> 57:43.166
Brendan, we're in
this together, okay?

57:43.168 --> 57:46.068
I mean all we have to do is
just get rid of the evidence,

57:46.070 --> 57:47.470
and everything's gonna be fine.

57:47.472 --> 57:48.604
We're not.

57:48.606 --> 57:50.472
We're not in anything together.

57:50.474 --> 57:53.209
Look I know when we first
got married it seemed

57:53.211 --> 57:55.211
like I was a very
adventurous person,

57:55.213 --> 57:58.180
but that was because we
were falling in love.

57:58.182 --> 58:01.283
You know, that was the
adventure, and to be honest,

58:01.285 --> 58:04.389
I've, I've never wanted
anything more than that.

58:05.791 --> 58:07.624
And I know you wanted to
do the talking fridge idea,

58:07.626 --> 58:12.631
I mean we should've, and we
didn't because I was afraid.

58:14.832 --> 58:18.535
And that's who I am, and you
deserve better than that,

58:18.537 --> 58:23.542
so all you gotta do is just
lay low for the next 24 hours,

58:24.910 --> 58:27.112
get on that plane, and
just get on with your life.

58:35.753 --> 58:37.053
Brendan
Hugh McCarthy?

58:37.055 --> 58:38.588
Yeah.

58:38.590 --> 58:40.256
I'm Detective Clifford,
this is Detective Coleman.

58:40.258 --> 58:42.258
You're under arrest on
suspicion of robbery,

58:42.260 --> 58:44.093
suspicion of
impersonating a guard,

58:44.095 --> 58:46.863
and the illegal possession
of a Garda uniform.

58:46.865 --> 58:48.330
You have the right
to remain silent.

58:48.332 --> 58:50.767
Anything you say can and
will be held against you

58:50.769 --> 58:51.736
in a court of law.

58:53.438 --> 58:57.106
Wait, Where are
you taking him?

58:57.108 --> 58:59.277
He'll have a chance to
phone you when he gets there.

59:19.264 --> 59:22.666
Yeah, that's right,
we have him now.

59:22.668 --> 59:23.501
Yeah.

59:53.064 --> 59:58.070
Well begod, hah?

59:58.936 --> 01:00:00.169
We got you, didn't we, Kieran?

01:00:00.171 --> 01:00:02.771
Oh we did, we definitely did.

01:00:02.773 --> 01:00:04.274
And you hadn't a
clue in the world

01:00:04.276 --> 01:00:06.242
that it was the pair of us
that was behind it, did you?

01:00:06.244 --> 01:00:07.376
What's going on?

01:00:07.378 --> 01:00:09.111
I'll tell you exactly
what's going on.

01:00:09.113 --> 01:00:11.780
First Kieran got me
by making me think

01:00:11.782 --> 01:00:13.749
that you had a gun pointed
to the back of my head.

01:00:13.751 --> 01:00:14.585
Top 29.

01:00:16.088 --> 01:00:18.220
Then yourself
and myself got him

01:00:18.222 --> 01:00:20.622
by making him think that I
was stone dead on the ground.

01:00:20.624 --> 01:00:22.124
Top 26.

01:00:22.126 --> 01:00:25.428
Then myself and himself
got you by making you think

01:00:25.430 --> 01:00:28.164
that you were after being
arrested for assaulting a guard.

01:00:28.166 --> 01:00:29.200
Top 17.

01:00:30.936 --> 01:00:35.939
And then you got us by
breaking into our house

01:00:35.941 --> 01:00:38.041
in the middle of the night.

01:00:38.043 --> 01:00:39.541
Top 32.

01:00:39.543 --> 01:00:42.512
And now we've got you
back even better than that

01:00:42.514 --> 01:00:44.814
by sending the lads
around to arrest you

01:00:44.816 --> 01:00:46.950
for stealing the
pair of our uniforms.

01:00:46.952 --> 01:00:48.117
Top 14.

01:00:48.119 --> 01:00:49.551
So you knew about that?

01:00:49.553 --> 01:00:51.521
Sure of course we did.

01:00:51.523 --> 01:00:53.923
And you very nearly
got away with it, too.

01:00:53.925 --> 01:00:56.658
It was only that I was
climbing back into the bed

01:00:56.660 --> 01:00:59.195
and I heard a noise from
outside the front of the house,

01:00:59.197 --> 01:01:01.330
and I got up and I looked out
the window, didn't I Kieran?

01:01:01.332 --> 01:01:02.599
Oh you did.

01:01:02.601 --> 01:01:04.633
Yeah, and when I saw
that it was your car

01:01:04.635 --> 01:01:06.269
that was driving away
into the distance,

01:01:06.271 --> 01:01:08.303
- do you know what I said?
- No.

01:01:08.305 --> 01:01:10.774
I said fair play
to that bastard.

01:01:10.776 --> 01:01:12.975
He got us an absolute beauty.

01:01:12.977 --> 01:01:14.376
And then do you
know what I said?

01:01:14.378 --> 01:01:15.912
No.

01:01:15.914 --> 01:01:17.780
I said we'll get him back an
even better beauty than that

01:01:17.782 --> 01:01:19.481
when we send the lads
around to arrest him

01:01:19.483 --> 01:01:21.316
and make him think he's
being taken off to the jail.

01:01:21.318 --> 01:01:22.619
Didn't I say that Kieran?

01:01:22.621 --> 01:01:24.019
Oh the very words,
Jim, the very words.

01:01:24.021 --> 01:01:26.189
So they said that
I was under suspicion

01:01:26.191 --> 01:01:27.689
of impersonating a guard

01:01:27.691 --> 01:01:30.292
'cause why else would
anyone steal Garda uniforms?

01:01:30.294 --> 01:01:33.729
But I was just getting ye back

01:01:33.731 --> 01:01:38.667
for the joke ye played on me
because I'm such a prankster.

01:01:38.669 --> 01:01:40.003
That's exactly it.

01:01:40.005 --> 01:01:43.405
So who's the bastard now, hah?

01:01:43.407 --> 01:01:45.742
Ye are, both of ye.

01:01:45.744 --> 01:01:49.579
You're definitely
a pair of bastards.

01:01:49.581 --> 01:01:50.916
And don't you forget it.

01:02:25.094 --> 01:02:27.427
But I honestly thought that
we were gonna get arrested,

01:02:27.429 --> 01:02:29.998
so I was just saying
whatever I needed to say

01:02:30.000 --> 01:02:32.500
to get you to go
safely back to America.

01:02:32.502 --> 01:02:34.835
So everything you said
this afternoon was a lie,

01:02:34.837 --> 01:02:36.570
but everything you told me

01:02:36.572 --> 01:02:38.306
before that this week
has been the truth?

01:02:38.308 --> 01:02:41.009
Well, no I mean, yes,

01:02:41.011 --> 01:02:44.145
I have been putting on
a kind of an act, but...

01:02:44.147 --> 01:02:46.346
I think I need to
use that plane ticket.

01:02:46.348 --> 01:02:47.614
What?

01:02:47.616 --> 01:02:50.050
I can be packed and
ready by tomorrow night.

01:02:50.052 --> 01:02:51.985
Nicole, we're not
going to get caught.

01:02:51.987 --> 01:02:53.520
I mean if the nun was
going to turn us in,

01:02:53.522 --> 01:02:54.788
she'd definitely
have done it by now.

01:02:54.790 --> 01:02:56.491
I just wish I'd stuck
to my original decision,

01:02:56.493 --> 01:02:58.092
and then we wouldn't be locked

01:02:58.094 --> 01:02:59.893
into this nonrefundable ticket,

01:02:59.895 --> 01:03:03.130
and we could've started
the divorce proceedings

01:03:03.132 --> 01:03:04.201
before I left.

01:03:05.268 --> 01:03:06.670
Divorce proceedings?

01:03:08.003 --> 01:03:10.471
But we've just had the
single greatest week

